The paper deals with the problem of computing the measure of regular sets of infinite binary trees, which is a topic in formal language theory and automata theory. The use of first-order formulas, Boolean combinations of conjunctive queries, and non-deterministic safety tree automata suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), and Information Theory (cs.IT).
